./CHANGELOG.md:44:- **Edge function (`supabase/functions/ai/index.ts`)** — Authenticated users only; model allowlist (OpenRouter IDs, e.g. `openai/gpt-3.5-turbo`, `openai/gpt-4o-mini`); message count and per-message length bounds; only `user`/`assistant` roles from clients; server-controlled system prompt prepended; temperature clamped to 0.0–2.0; OpenRouter failures return generic client messages while details are logged server-side; top-level errors do not leak internal exception text
./CHANGELOG.md:50:- **PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy** — Privacy manifest declaring UserDefaults API usage (required for App Store)
./CHANGELOG.md:170:New FeatureRating module for smart, sentiment-based app rating prompts. Track positive and negative user actions, automatically show a beautiful pre-prompt popup at the right moment, and trigger the native App Store review dialog when users are happiest.
./CHANGELOG.md:180:- `RatingEngine` with sentiment scoring, time-based decay, and smart decision logic
./CHANGELOG.md:181:- `RatingStorage` protocol with `UserDefaultsRatingStorage` implementation
./CHANGELOG.md:307:Major update with OneSignal push notifications integration and critical session management fix. Users now stay logged in reliably across app restarts.
./CHANGELOG.md:317:- Secure configuration via `Config/Secrets.xcconfig` (ONESIGNAL_APP_ID)
./CHANGELOG.md:337:Users were being unexpectedly logged out when opening the app after the access token expired (~1 hour). This was a critical bug affecting user experience.
./CHANGELOG.md:345:- Only logs out user if ALL refresh attempts fail (refresh token expired/revoked)
./CHANGELOG.md:357:| Open app after 2 hours | ✅ Silent refresh, stays logged in |
./CHANGELOG.md:358:| Open app after 3 days | ✅ Silent refresh, stays logged in |
./CHANGELOG.md:359:| Open app after 14+ days | Graceful logout (refresh token expired) |
./CHANGELOG.md:370:- Updated `scripts/update-config.sh` to handle ONESIGNAL_APP_ID validation
./CHANGELOG.md:379:  - New troubleshooting section for unexpected logout issues
./CHANGELOG.md:386:  - Verbose logging in DEBUG builds
